<Author>popelsmom
<Content>Old and Run Down Stayed at the hotel on Nov. 14, 2008. We purchased a package that included free transportation from the cruise terminal and a free shuttle to the airport the next morning. The staff was very accomodating. I called the hotel to get a ride from the cruise pier and they had housekeeping get a room ready for us even though check in wasn't until the afternoon. That was nice because we had an exhausted three year old. The hotel is in a good location, but is very run down and in need of major improvements. It is located right next to a public bus stop that we used to go downtown to the Bayside Park. The bus system is very good in Miami.We were supposed to have two double beds but they gave us a king instead. I didn't complain, it was big enough for the three of us. The floors were very dirty and there was hair on the floor in the bathroom. I was a bit disgusted but we were really only there to sleep for one night. There is free wifi throughout the building and a tiny breakfast of packaged, expired foods in the morning. I suggest walking to one of the nearby restaurants, like Denny's. They have a pool that is really small, I didn't use it. The transportation included in the price makes the stay worth it, but I would pay more next time for a better hotel. 
