<Author>sassy0930
<Content>Great for us This hotel was perfect for my husband and I. We stayed over for one night before a cruise and it was all we needed. It had no extra perks really. The rooms were clean and the man behind the desk was friendly enough. There were plenty of places to eat within a couple of blocks so we could walk to them all. Only a couple of miles from the port so when we left in the morning it was easy to get out.It's not a luxury hotel with all the amenities, but if all you need is a bed and a roof over your head this place is ok. If you are a sinbgle traveler you may want to consider a safer locale though. My husband was offered drugs in between the hotel and the gas station across the street! But a polite no thank you took care of that issue. I felt very safe while we were there. 
