<Author>ghutch
<Content>Roaches carried us away have you ever seen that commercial where the couple get married and he takes her back to his place, to which she applies a paper bag to her face and starts to hyperventilate? yea, we lived that commercial.i could sum it all up (but i wont) by saying that when we asked if there was an elevator (dont even think you will get help with your bags) i never heard so much laughter, hey, did you hear what they just asked? ha!!figuring we are staying only one night prior to our cruise, we could tough it out, being from new england - no problem! so, we take a bus to south beach (which was the smartest way to travel), and upon returning we decided to retire for the evening. after taking a frigid shower (to which we complained and got the response-i'll have somebody look into that. - yea, right!), we layed down on the bed to watch a little t.v. Well, after a couple of minutes my peripheral vision develops a severe case of roach-itis! i jumped up, wacked the bugs, told the wife to pack our bags, put the bugs in a cup and took them to the front desk. the man was very apologetic and even offered another room. yea, no thanks! expedia found us a room at the days inn on south beach within minutes, although explaining that we are going from a 3 star room to a 1 and a half! let me just say that whatever system they are using to rate these hotels is severely busted! so at 10pm we are taking the bus back over to south beach, thankfully reimbursed, yet forever scorned.do yourself a favor and spend a few extra dollars! 
