<Author>Jim1857
<Content>Feb 2004 Terrible A real horror story. I stayed here for two nights (prior to our cruise) with eight other couples. All the couples had their own rooms. My room was small, dirty  one flight up. I had booked poolside. The front desk changed it to a poolside room. The poolside room bathroom window had no glass  no screen. Soap was a small white piece (brown-stained) from age. The toilet bowl and sink never stopped running. The pillows probably were many years old. The air conditioner was icy cold but so loud you couldn't hear the T.V. I couldn't change my room because the hotel was full. The other couples had similar complaints with their rooms including a broken leg on one bed, collapsed mattress on another bed, curtains that didn't close fully for privacy, etc. We all experienced the inablilty to get fresh towels until after 5P.M. on both nights (because the hotel washing machine was broken). A total of 5 lounge chairs were around the pool for the booked-full hotel guests to use.Complaints to the front desk (in person) were unanswered. We were stuck there for 2 nights awaiting our cruise ship.Returning from my cruise vacation, I wrote to Super 8 corporation as well as the hotel directly. To date, I've received no replies.We paid about $90.00/night. I realize Super 8 is not on top of the hotel chains, but this property comes close to violating some local ordinances and/or health codes. My advice is to go for the extra bucks and stay at a better hotel in Miami. 
